I thought about posting the one who ruined my life.
Because when I got Internet I sought to see what my memory of her really was.
That introduced me to furry art, and wasted the hours I should've spent usefully, becoming a contender and a success in life.
(And there are something like two or three furries who are the only ones who remember the character and draw/comm her, and I don't want to be mistaken for one of them, no shade, just no connection.)

I'm happy keeping my memory of her my private secret.

I only saw the show a few times, and she was a second tier cast member so when I did see she wouldn't necessarily be featured.
But even though I was too young to "get it," I remember feeling jealous when it was implied that one of the furbois was her boyfriend.
I've thought about looking up the show again, but I fear that it might be crap (well, I know it was crap but that her character/voice/whatever might be crap, too) and ruin the memory.

But time and time again, when I write or I draw, and I find myself liking a female character a bit more than just any character, I think of my memory of Her, and I see why.

And I wonder if that prototype of femininity, perhaps a completely mistaken one, is the standard I've sought, and never found in the flesh.

To this day I've thought it was bad luck and my personality, but maybe it's just that they don't make real women like the anthro woman who set my standards.
